abstract: Democratic and Republican officials alike turn their backs on what should be a scandal of justice and race.

abstract: Plaintiffs in several lawsuits against Wells Fargo accuse the bank of failing to notify them when it changed loan repayment plans.
snippet: Plaintiffs in several lawsuits against Wells Fargo accuse the bank of failing to notify them when it changed loan repayment plans.
lead_paragraph: The prospect of your bank adjusting your mortgage and lowering those monthly payments probably seems quite attractive, especially if you’re in bankruptcy.

abstract: Some saw a fleeting moment in a contentious hearing, this time of Attorney General Jeff Sessions. Others saw a pattern of sexism.
snippet: Some saw a fleeting moment in a contentious hearing, this time of Attorney General Jeff Sessions. Others saw a pattern of sexism.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris, Democrat of California, was cut off by Republican senators on Tuesday as she questioned Attorney General Jeff Sessions during the latest high-profile Senate Intelligence Committee hearing in its investigation into Russian election interference.

headline_main: Kamala Harris Is (Again) Interrupted While Pressing a Senate Witness

abstract: Senator Kamala Harris and Attorney General Jeff Sessions had a contentious back and forth at a Senate Intelligence hearing, at which Senator Richard Burr, the committee chairman, had to weigh in.
snippet: Senator Kamala Harris and Attorney General Jeff Sessions had a contentious back and forth at a Senate Intelligence hearing, at which Senator Richard Burr, the committee chairman, had to weigh in.

abstract: Mr. Sessions called any suggestion that he colluded with Russians an “appalling” lie. He refused to talk about his communications with the president.
snippet: Mr. Sessions called any suggestion that he colluded with Russians an “appalling” lie. He refused to talk about his communications with the president.
lead_paragraph: Attorney General Jeff Sessions engaged in highly contentious testimony before the Senate Intelligence Committee on Tuesday, with Democrats pressing him on his conversations with President Trump related to the investigation of Russian meddling in the 2016 election. He called any suggestion that he colluded with Russians during the election an “appalling” lie. “Please, colleagues, hear me on this,” he said.

abstract: Washington was braced for high drama as the deposed F.B.I. director testified before a Senate committee. And James Comey delivered, with a gift for narrative and a dose of humility.
snippet: Washington was braced for high drama as the deposed F.B.I. director testified before a Senate committee. And James Comey delivered, with a gift for narrative and a dose of humility.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On the 140th day of the Trump presidency — one for each allotted character on the executive Twitter feed that stayed conspicuously silent all Thursday morning — a very tall man with a very strange place in this very bewildering moment in American history strolled into Hart Senate Office Building 216, shot a quick glance at the masses arrayed behind him and presented a seen-it-all city with something unusual.

headline_main: Comey: Hero, Villain and Shakespearean Character Who Lived Up to Hype
headline_print_headline: A Hero, Villain and Shakespearean Character Who Lived Up to the Hype

abstract: James B. Comey, the nation’s former top lawman, methodically detailed a story of being awkwardly courted and pressured by a chief executive he could not trust.
snippet: James B. Comey, the nation’s former top lawman, methodically detailed a story of being awkwardly courted and pressured by a chief executive he could not trust.
lead_paragraph: In any reality-TV show — if we can agree that that is what American politics has morphed into — there comes the moment where one of the stars reads his or her co-stars for filth. Sue Hawk delivered her famous “rat and snake” speech about her opponents on the first season of “Survivor.” Teresa Giudice flipped over a table on “The Real Housewives of New Jersey.”
